<synopsis><code mime="text/x-python">
@accepts(gfloat)
@returns(none)
def set_width(width)
</code></synopsis>
<p>Forces a width on an actor, causing the actor's preferred width
and height (if any) to be ignored.</p><p>If @width is -1 the actor will use its preferred width request
instead of overriding it, i.e. you can "unset" the width with -1.</p><p>This function sets both the minimum and natural size of the actor.</p>

<table>
<tr>
<td><p>width :</p></td>
<td><p>Requested new width for the actor, in pixels, or -1</p></td>
</tr>
</table>
